.TH "TD\-DIFF" "1" "2026" "TARDIS Manual"
.SH NAME
td\-diff \- compute the difference between two dates
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]td diff\f[R] \f[I]DATE1\f[R] \f[I]DATE2\f[R] [\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]td diff\f[R] computes the duration between two date expressions and
prints the result.
By default, the output is a human\-readable duration string
(e.g.\ \[lq]2 months, 14 days\[rq]).
Alternative output formats include total seconds and ISO 8601 duration.
.PP
Both \f[I]DATE1\f[R] and \f[I]DATE2\f[R] accept the same
natural\-language expressions as the main \f[B]td\f[R] command,
including epoch timestamps with the **\[at]** prefix.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-o\f[R], \f[B]\-\-output\f[R] \f[I]FORMAT\f[R]
Select the diff output format.
Accepted values:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]human\f[R] \[en] Human\-readable duration (default).
Example: \[lq]2 months, 14 days\[rq].
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]seconds\f[R] \[en] Total seconds between the two dates.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]iso\f[R] \[en] ISO 8601 duration format.
Example: \[lq]P2M14D\[rq].
.RE
.TP
\f[B]\-j\f[R], \f[B]\-\-json\f[R]
Output as a JSON object.
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\-\-no\-newline\f[R]
Suppress the trailing newline.
.TP
\f[B]\-\-now\f[R] \f[I]DATETIME\f[R]
Override the current time (RFC 3339).
.TP
\f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\-\-timezone\f[R] \f[I]TZ\f[R]
Timezone for resolution (IANA/Olson ID).
.TP
\f[B]\-v\f[R], \f[B]\-\-verbose\f[R]
Print verbose diagnostics to stderr.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\-\-help\f[R]
Print help information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Basic difference between two dates:
.IP
.EX
td diff \[dq]2025\-01\-01\[dq] \[dq]2025\-03\-15\[dq] \-\-now 2025\-01\-01T00:00:00Z \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Output as total seconds:
.IP
.EX
td diff \[dq]2025\-01\-01\[dq] \[dq]2025\-06\-01\[dq] \-\-output seconds \-\-now 2025\-01\-01T00:00:00Z \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Output as ISO 8601 duration:
.IP
.EX
td diff \[dq]2025\-01\-01\[dq] \[dq]2025\-03\-15\[dq] \-\-output iso \-\-now 2025\-01\-01T00:00:00Z \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
JSON output:
.IP
.EX
td diff yesterday tomorrow \-\-json \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T12:00:00Z \-t UTC
.EE
.PP
Timezone\-aware diff:
.IP
.EX
td diff \[dq]2025\-01\-01\[dq] \[dq]2025\-07\-01\[dq] \-t America/New_York \-\-now 2025\-01\-01T00:00:00Z
.EE
.PP
With \[en]now for deterministic scripting:
.IP
.EX
td diff \[dq]now\[dq] \[dq]next friday\[dq] \-\-now 2025\-06\-24T09:00:00Z \-t UTC
.EE
